{"id":32132,"title":"Spiritual care in a crisis: what is enough?","abstract":"Nurses encounter crisis regularly. What are appropriate spiritual interventions? Christians are encouraged to use every opportunity to be a witness for Christ. Should nurses share their faith in times of crisis? The experience of a nurse caring for a mother after perinatal loss is explored by a philosopher, mental health clinical nurse specialist, and the nurse, who wonders if she should have done things differently.","date":"2014-07-09","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25004727","annotations":[{"name":"Mental health","weight":0.816331,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mental_health"},{"name":"Spirituality","weight":0.810495,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spirituality"},{"name":"Pregnancy","weight":0.796625,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pregnancy"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.781524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Nurse","weight":0.687788,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nurse"},{"name":"Philosophy","weight":0.548236,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophy"},{"name":"Mind","weight":0.372176,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mind"},{"name":"Faith","weight":0.325361,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faith"},{"name":"Christian","weight":0.289179,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christian"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.286427,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"},{"name":"Christ","weight":0.152154,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christ"},{"name":"Witness","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witness"},{"name":"Clinical nurse specialist","weight":0.0447457,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_nurse_specia